&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 7 Tissue Viability Clinical Nurse Specialist to join the Tissue Viability clinical Nurse Specialist team at The Royal Marsden Hospital. &lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant should have experience in tissue viability and should be passionate about providing expert advice and education, which will support the clinical teams to deliver safe, compassionate care, reduce harm and improve patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to work as a self-directed practitioner and have strong team working relationships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be flexible and able to work on both the Sutton and Chelsea site. This post is advertised as a 1 year fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anna Collins, Matron, anna.collins@rmh.nhs.uk, 020 8642 6011 cordless 1763&lt;/p&gt;
